# 🔁 3. Pattern 1: Traversal (Basic but Powerful)

👉 Visit every element

```js
let arr = [1, 2, 3, 4];

for (let i = 0; i < arr.length; i++) {
  console.log(arr[i]);
}
```

---

### 💡 Use cases:

* Sum of array
* Count elements
* Find max/min

---

### 🧪 Example:

```js
// Find max
let max = arr[0];
for (let i = 1; i < arr.length; i++) {
  if (arr[i] > max) max = arr[i];
}
```

---

# 👯 4. Pattern 2: Two Pointer (VERY IMPORTANT 🔥)

👉 Use two indices instead of one

---

### 📌 When to use:

* Sorted arrays
* Pairs problem

---

### 🧪 Example: Pair with sum = target

```js
let arr = [1, 2, 3, 4, 6];
let left = 0, right = arr.length - 1;
let target = 6;

while (left < right) {
  let sum = arr[left] + arr[right];
  
  if (sum === target) {
    console.log(arr[left], arr[right]);
    break;
  } else if (sum < target) {
    left++;
  } else {
    right--;
  }
}
```

---

# 🪟 5. Pattern 3: Sliding Window (INTERVIEW FAVORITE)

👉 Work on subarrays efficiently

---

### ❌ Brute force:

Nested loops → slow

---

### ✅ Optimized:

```js
let arr = [2, 1, 5, 1, 3, 2];
let k = 3;

let windowSum = 0;

// first window
for (let i = 0; i < k; i++) {
  windowSum += arr[i];
}

let maxSum = windowSum;

// slide window
for (let i = k; i < arr.length; i++) {
  windowSum += arr[i] - arr[i - k];
  maxSum = Math.max(maxSum, windowSum);
}

console.log(maxSum);
```

---

### 💡 Use cases:

* Max sum subarray
* Longest substring
* Fixed window problems

---

# ➕ 6. Pattern 4: Prefix Sum

👉 Precompute sums to answer fast

---

### 🧪 Example:

```js
let arr = [1, 2, 3, 4];
let prefix = [];

prefix[0] = arr[0];

for (let i = 1; i < arr.length; i++) {
  prefix[i] = prefix[i - 1] + arr[i];
}

// sum from index 1 to 3
let sum = prefix[3] - prefix[0];
console.log(sum);
```

---

### 💡 Use cases:

* Range sum queries
* Subarray problems

---

# ⚡ 7. Pattern 5: Kadane’s Algorithm (🔥 MUST KNOW)

👉 Maximum subarray sum

---

\text{maxEnding} = \max(a_i, \text{maxEnding} + a_i)

---

### 🧪 Code:

```js
let arr = [-2, 1, -3, 4, -1, 2, 1, -5, 4];

let maxSum = arr[0];
let currentSum = arr[0];

for (let i = 1; i < arr.length; i++) {
  currentSum = Math.max(arr[i], currentSum + arr[i]);
  maxSum = Math.max(maxSum, currentSum);
}

console.log(maxSum);
```

---

# 🔍 8. Pattern 6: Sorting + Searching

---

### Binary Search (Sorted array only)

```js
let left = 0, right = arr.length - 1;

while (left <= right) {
  let mid = Math.floor((left + right) / 2);

  if (arr[mid] === target) return mid;
  else if (arr[mid] < target) left = mid + 1;
  else right = mid - 1;
}
```

---

### 💡 Time complexity:

* Binary search → **O(log n)** 🚀

